50|$|The {{stratopause}} (formerly <b>Mesopeak)</b> is {{the level}} of the atmosphere which is the boundary between two layers: the stratosphere and the mesosphere. In the stratosphere the temperature increases with altitude, and the stratopause is the region where a maximum in the temperature occurs.This atmospheric feature is not only associated with Earth: it occurs on any other planet or moon that has an atmosphere as well.|$|E

